==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skeg
<hw>Skeg</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov. E., also a stump
of a branch, a wooden peg; cf. Icel. <ets>sk<?/gr</ets> a wood, Sw.
<ets>skog</ets>. Cf. <er>Shaw</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sort of
wild plum.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>A kind of oats.</def> <rj><au>Farm.
Encyc.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>The after part of the keel of a
vessel, to which the rudder is attached.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skegger</ent>⟦br⟧
